commit_list.message: Update has many through post title
Remove the welcome to Jekyll post
Move library files into transportdata directory
End search early if it meets certain conditions
Export all types that may be used outside package.
Refactor: store graph in search state

Refactor: Introduce search state struct

This decouples the graph data structure from the search state, so that
the same graph can cleanly be re-used for multiple searches.

Reimplement search using priority queue

This implementation is around 3-5x faster, and offloads some of the
complexity to the priority queue data structure.

Refactor PathSearch function

* Introduced pathSearchState struct to hold search state
* Extracted methods from PathSearch on to pathSearchState struct
* Added missing error handling
PathSearch now returns path of node IDs
Add benchmark and extract test setup function

Shortest distance search using Dijkstras algorithm

http://everythingcomputerscience.com/algorithms/Dijkstras_Algorithm.html
Extract making csv reader into func
Index stops by ID, not name
Add graph package with StopNode type
Add script for downloading GTFS data
Add script for loading CSV data into SQL database

Change path to slice of edge

Also changed internal state maps to use pointers to vertices rather than
the vertexID field as their keys.

Use path String() method in tests

Also don't return anything from search function.
Move graph and vertex types to own files
Add readme with Travis build status

Remove original implementation

Removed the original shortest path search implementation and replaced it
with the priority queue based implementation.

Fix amazon instance type on build an image page

This page referred to using a "t1.micro" instance but the template actually uses a "t2.micro".

Remove the composer path config

Going to look into using the Laravel VM thing instead.
Add composer php binaries to path 😱
Add "web" which serves the current directory
Alter settings for latest neovim version
A couple of neoterm config improvements

Remove tmux related vim plugins

As I don't use tmux anymore.
Add leader mapping for opening a new terminal
Add an extra key binding for terminal panes

Use jellybeans as default colorscheme

Also turned on 24 bit colour in Neovim, which makes things look nicer.
Add key mappings for Neovim terminal mode
Remove "tagbar" plugin, since I never use it

Add key binding for CtrlPBufTag command

This command lets you search for a tag within the current buffer and
jump to the definition.
Set syntastic checkers based on project config

Add shell config for nodejs

* Setup node version manager, which is a sort of equivalent to rbenv.
* Adds per-project binaries from npm to $PATH.
Add tagbar plugin and open with <F6>
Use eslint in project node_modules dir
Add key binding to show git status

Set git "push.default" to "current"

This should mean I can now run "git push -u" and have the equivalent
remote branch be created automatically as part of the push. This is
better than using the "create-branch" script because that creates the
remote branch immediately, which triggers CI despite there being no
actual changes yet.

Description from git manual:

"current - push the current branch to update a branch with the same name
on the receiving end. Works in both central and non-central workflows".

Customise my "gitmessage" template

__Why was this change necessary?__

To make good commit messages easier to write.

__How does it address the problem?__

By changing the contents of "~/.gitmessage".

Allow resizing tmux panes using the mouse

Terminal.app in 10.11 seems to have added better mouse support, so may
as well enable this.

Fix for <ctrl-h> key binding in Neovim

https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/2048#issuecomment-78045837

Update key binding for clearing search highlight

Previously it conflicted with vim-rspec.

Add mapping to toggle search highlighting

Neovim enables "hlsearch" by default, so it's useful to be able to
toggle the highlighting off easily.
Remove plugins that are problematic with Neovim

Add mapping to search for word under cursor

https://robots.thoughtbot.com/faster-grepping-in-vim
Syntax highlight EJS templates as HTML
Only use Dispatch in terminal vim

* Also add base16 colorscheme plugin
No need to add Homebrew bin dirs to PATH
Don't run rbenv init in zshrc.local

* Use solarized light color scheme
